cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with a deep learning model for segmenting brain tissue from MRI scans, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of dilated convolutions and the focus on reducing errors suggests an emphasis on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the potential clinical applications of the model suggest a connection to medical imaging (cs.MM).
